data.name: 0000 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Me and Nagato met up with Haruhi in the corridor with all the first year classrooms.

data.name: 0001 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Oh, where's Mikuru and Koiuzmi?

data.name: 0002 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: That's what Haruhi asked, but I avoided tell- ing her that they'd gone to the computer lab.

data.name: 0003 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Now then, at the end of this long corridor on the main building's third floor, is Class 1-9.

data.name: 0004 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I'm truly grateful. Please let it stay this way.

data.name: 0005 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Hey, Haruhi, there is no Class 1-10 here.

data.name: 0006 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: That's only natural, Kyon. One of the seven wonders isn't just going to appear that easily.

data.name: 0007 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It appeared that easily in front of me, but I can never tell Haruhi that.

data.name: 0008 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: I reckon there's some kind of condition to trigger it. Investigate every nook and cranny!

data.name: 0009 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: If you see any unusual signs, report back to your Brigade Chief immediately.

data.name: 0010 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Let's go okay?

data.name: 0011 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Haruhi alone is enthusiastic, going up and down the long corridor.

data.name: 0012 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Room 7, 8, 9... Hmm... There's no unnatural phenomena here is there?

data.name: 0013 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: There's not. Just an ordinary hallway. Maybe they were just seeing things after all?

data.name: 0014 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: No, there's something here.

data.name: 0015 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: I'm sure of it! The "man-eating classroom" Class 1-10 that's been long plaguing North High!

data.name: 0016 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Stuff gets mixed up before you know it. Long? I only heard about it today.

data.name: 0017 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: But maybe it won't appear in front of normal humans. Like you might need psychic powers.

data.name: 0018 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: If it's espers you need I happen to know one.

data.name: 0019 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Maybe the Computer Society member who said he witnessed it just made a mistake.

data.name: 0020 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Listen here, Kyon.

data.name: 0021 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: It's a bad habit for an SOS Brigade member to say something so lacking in imagination.

data.name: 0022 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: I believe in it. Even ghosts and unnatural phenomena exist!

data.name: 0023 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: The SOS Brigade was created for the sake of searching for them.

data.name: 0024 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I guess so. However…

data.name: 0025 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Things like ghosts and unnatural phenomena? To tell you the truth I've seen them.

data.name: 0026 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Incidentally, I don't have any psychic powers. No guardian angel either of course.

data.name: 0027 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: When cats or babies look at the sky when there's nothing there, they see ghosts right?

data.name: 0028 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Oh yeah, Yuki, you also stare at thin air sometimes don't you. Just like a cat.

data.name: 0029 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: I do not see ghosts.

data.name: 0030 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: In Nagato's case, she probably sees electromagnetic radiation or something.

data.name: 0031 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: I feel like out of all of us Yuki might have the best affinity for sensing the supernatural.

data.name: 0032 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Don't you think, Kyon?

data.name: 0033 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato... Indeed might be a kind of like a cat.

data.name: 0034 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Right! That's why I think her sensing abilities are strong.

data.name: 0035 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: That's not related to psychic powers though.

data.name: 0036 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: No, it is related. Without a doubt.

data.name: 0037 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: In that case, can you not sense the supernatural because you're like a dog?

data.name: 0038 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: You're the one who's like a dog.

data.name: 0039 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: If anything you're a polar bear... Or a sealion maybe.

data.name: 0040 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: As usual she says something awful. Just how do you perceive me?

data.name: 0041 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: If I were a dog, I'd be a really impressive one.

data.name: 0042 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: The kind that would win the championship in a dog contest.

data.name: 0043 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: You'd never win. You wouldn't listen to your owner at all.

data.name: 0044 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: That's right. I don't need an owner, I'm more like a lone wolf.

data.name: 0045 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: ...Wolves are in packs. They are not alone.

data.name: 0046 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nice straight man, Nagato.

data.name: 0047 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: I see. Then, being the wolf boss is fine.

data.name: 0048 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato doesn't seem like a psychic. Isn't she more like an ultra realist?

data.name: 0049 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: That's why she seems like a cat.

data.name: 0050 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: I think there's almost certainly a mistake with a diagram that says cat = spiritual radar.

data.name: 0051 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Although I do admit she's like one.

data.name: 0052 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: What are the characteristics of a cat's appearance?

data.name: 0053 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Listen Nagato, there are different types. There's cat-like people and dog-like people.

data.name: 0054 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: It's a rough estimate analysis of someone's personality.

data.name: 0055 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Yuki, let out a little "meow" sound!

data.name: 0056 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Oi, don't mess with Nagato.

data.name: 0057 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Meow.

data.name: 0058 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: No no no, do it with more emotion.

data.name: 0059 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Meow.

data.name: 0060 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Hmm, something's off.

data.name: 0061 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Haruhi, knock it off.

data.name: 0062 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Anyways, use your abilities to search for the supernatural Yuki! Please do it!

data.name: 0063 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: As I said, there's no connection at all.

data.name: 0064 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Okay, Yuki, go!

data.name: 0066 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Haruhi starts leading Nagato away.

data.name: 0067 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Do you sense anything suspicious over there?

data.name: 0068 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Nothing.

data.name: 0069 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Then, is there something out of the ordinary over here?

data.name: 0070 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: An existence cannot be confirmed.

data.name: 0071 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: There's gotta be something here!

data.name: 0072 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Nothing is detected.

data.name: 0073 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It's like they're searching for stolen goods with a police dog, but can't find anything.

data.name: 0074 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Please don't find anything. But even if you do, don't tell Haruhi.

data.name: 0075 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Hey, this hallway, doesn't it look different from normal?

data.name: 0076 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: There are no people.

data.name: 0077 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Also it's more gloomy than usual.

data.name: 0078 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Because of summer vacation the lights are off.

data.name: 0079 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Ah! Something just flew past the window just now! A mysterious flying object!

data.name: 0080 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: A ball.

data.name: 0081 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Ahhh, the baseball club must have come to practice.

data.name: 0082 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: What was that weird sound? It sounds like a poltergeist!

data.name: 0083 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: The baseball club is just making noise during practice.

data.name: 0084 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: It is the sound of a ball coming into contact with a bat, and then into contact with a mitt.

data.name: 0085 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: …There's nothing here. Boring.

data.name: 0086 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: That's why I said the unnatural phenomenon was just a hoax.

data.name: 0087 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: It's just that the conditions haven't been satisfied yet. We need to acquire more info.

data.name: 0088 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: I'm gonna go back for a while and re-examine what we know.

data.name: 0089 (373.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Kyon and Yuki, please search for leads.

data.name: 0090 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Haruhi said over her shoulder while leaving.

data.name: 0091 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Looks like she got bored. Thank goodness nothing happened.

data.name: 0092 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Hey, Nagato, has anything changed since the information couplings became unstable?

data.name: 0094 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato?

data.name: 0095 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Nagato's gaze is fixed on a single point in space.

data.name: 0096 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: As Haruhi said, her condition certainly seems very cat-like, but…

data.name: 0097 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It's already ominous when a cat does it, but if it's Nagato that makes me even more anxious.

data.name: 0098 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato, is there something there?

data.name: 0099 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I can't see anything strange at the point she's staring at.

data.name: 0100 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Maybe she's receiving scattered radio waves to verify the school's condition or something.

data.name: 0101 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I'd rather you not call Nagato a psychic girl.

data.name: 0102 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Well, not that her abilities are practically that different, I just mean emotionally.

data.name: 0103 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: It is spreading.

data.name: 0104 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: What is?

data.name: 0105 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: The information couplings are becoming more unstable due to abnormal space developing.

data.name: 0106 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: So you were verifying the whole thing after all.

data.name: 0107 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: But it's spreading huh. It might be best to get Haruhi to leave the school.

data.name: 0108 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: There is an increase in abnormal phenomenon activity by means of Haruhi Suzumiya's desire.

data.name: 0109 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Eh? That's...

data.name: 0110 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Over there…

data.name: 0111 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Nagato pointed to outside the window.

data.name: 0112 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Actually, maybe she checked the entire school because of my question.

data.name: 0113 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I wonder if she was receiving radio waves invisible to the outside observer.

data.name: 0114 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I'm starting to get worried.

data.name: 0115 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: With Nagato, this isn't some joke or pun, it's reality.

data.name: 0116 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: The information couplings are becoming more unstable due to abnormal space developing.

data.name: 0117 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: I see.

data.name: 0118 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It didn't seem like there was anything there. I'm glad I didn't ask.

data.name: 0119 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Abnormal phenomena is increasing by means of Haruhi Suzumiya's desire. For example…

data.name: 0120 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Nagato suddenly pointed outside the window.

data.name: 0121 (373.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Over there.

data.name: 0122 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: There's nothing there?

data.name: 0124 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Nagato responded to my doubt by looking up at me in silence.

data.name: 0126 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: But she turned back and walked away without offering any explanation.

data.name: 0127 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: …What did she mean?

data.name: 0128 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: "You can't see it?" I wonder if that was the nuance.

data.name: 0129 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I once more looked out the window to find nothing.

data.name: 0130 (373.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: I can't see anything. Which is equivalent to nothing existing!

data.name: 0131 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I tried to convince myself as I chased after Nagato.

data.name: 0132 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: When we were looking around here with Haruhi, just what did Nagato see?

data.name: 0133 (373.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I became worried all over again.

data.name: 0134 (373.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: She does seem like a cat.

data.name: 0135 (373.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: I don't think so.

data.name: 0136 (373.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Ask Nagato.

data.name: 0137 (373.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Don't ask Nagato.
